igns/downloads/528/exotic_pet_-_executive_summary26_09.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://eurogroupforanimals.org/files/campaigns/downloads/528/exotic_pet_-_executive_summary26_09.pdf</span></a><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_edn12"></a><a href="#_ednref12">[xii]</a><span style="font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt"> Soulsbury, Carl D.</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt">, Iossa, Graziella, Kennell, Sarah and Harris, Stephen (2009) ‘The Welfare and Suitability of Primates Kept as Pets’, Journal of Applied Animal Welfare Science, 12:1, 1-20. doi:10.1080/10888700802536483</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_edn13"></a><a href="#_ednref13">[xiii]</a><span style="font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt"> Schroepfer KK, Rosati AG, Chartrand T, Hare B (2011</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt">) Use of “Entertainment” Chimpanzees in Commercials Distorts Public Perception Regarding Their Conservation Status. PLoS ONE 6(10):e26048. doi:10.1371/journal.pone.0026048</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt"><a name="_edn14"></a><a href="#_ednref14">[xiv]</a><span style="font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt"> Federation of Veterinarians of Europe (2013) ‘Keeping wild animals and other exoti</span><span style="font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt">c animals as companion animals’, FVE/013/pos/006,</span><a href="http://www.fve.org/uploads/publications/docs/006_fve_position_on_positive_lists_of_exotic_species_final.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.fve.org/uploads/publications/docs/006_fve_position_on_positive_lists_of_exo</span><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Arial Narrow'; font-size:9pt; text-decoration:underline